    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "### Describe the bug\n\nCasting ctuples fails with C compilation error.\n\n### Code to reproduce the behaviour:\n\n```cython\ndef main():\n    cdef tuple[float, float] t = (1.0, 2.0)\n    x1 = cython.cast(tuple[int, int], t)\nmain()\n```\nor:\n```cython\ndef main():\n    cdef (float, float) t = (1.0, 2.0)\n    x1 = cython.cast((int, int), t)\nmain()\n```\n\n### Expected behaviour\n\nC compiler should not fail.\n\n### OS\n\nLinux\n\n### Python version\n\n3.14\n\n### Cython version\n\nmaster\n\n### Additional context\n\nFollowing errors return GCC:\n```c\n[1/1] Cythonizing /home/dev/cython/test/a.pyx\n/home/dev/cython/test/a.c: In function ‘__pyx_pf_1a_main’:\n/home/dev/cython/test/a.c:2461:62: error: incompatible type for argument 1 of ‘__pyx_convert__to_py___pyx_ctuple_int__and_int’\n 2461 |   __pyx_t_2 = __pyx_convert__to_py___pyx_ctuple_int__and_int(__pyx_v_t); if (unlikely(!__pyx_t_2)) __PYX_ERR(0, 86, __pyx_L1_error)\n      |                                                              ^~~~~~~~~\n      |                                                              |\n      |                                                              __pyx_ctuple_float__and_float\n/home/dev/cython/test/a.c:2112:65: note: expected ‘__pyx_ctuple_int__and_int’ but argument is of type ‘__pyx_ctuple_float__and_float’\n 2112 | static PyObject* __pyx_convert__to_py___pyx_ctuple_int__and_int(__pyx_ctuple_int__and_int);\n      |                                                                 ^~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~\nerror: command '/usr/bin/cc' failed with exit code 1\n```\n\nOr:\n\n```c\n[1/1] Cythonizing /home/dev/cython/test/a.pyx\n/home/dev/cython/test/a.c:2098:1: error: parameter names (without types) in function declaration [-Wdeclaration-missing-parameter-type]\n 2098 | static PyObject* __pyx_convert__to_py___pyx_ctuple_int__and_int(__pyx_ctuple_int__and_int);\n      | ^~~~~~\n/home/dev/cython/test/a.c:5489:65: error: unknown type name ‘__pyx_ctuple_int__and_int’; did you mean ‘__pyx_ctuple_float__and_float’?\n 5489 | static PyObject* __pyx_convert__to_py___pyx_ctuple_int__and_int(__pyx_ctuple_int__and_int value) {\n      |                                                                 ^~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~\n      |                                                                 __pyx_ctuple_float__and_float\n/home/dev/cython/test/a.c:2098:18: warning: ‘__pyx_convert__to_py___pyx_ctuple_int__and_int’ used but never defined\n 2098 | static PyObject* __pyx_convert__to_py___pyx_ctuple_int__and_int(__pyx_ctuple_int__and_int);\n      |                  ^~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~\nerror: command '/usr/bin/cc' failed with exit code 1\n```",
